---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words with Prefix DOWN in Scrabble — Top Scoring Words & Strategy Guide"
  description="Master DOWN prefix words in Scrabble. Top plays include DOWNLOAD, DOWNSIZE, DOWNHILL, DOWNTOWN, DOWNTURN. 4-tile prefix worth 8 points — W(4) gives strong base."
  keywords="words with prefix down scrabble, down words scrabble, download scrabble, down prefix strategy, downtown scrabble points, scrabble words starting with down"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article", "headline": "Words with Prefix DOWN in Scrabble — Top Scoring Words & Strategy Guide", "description": "Master DOWN prefix words in Scrabble. 4-tile prefix worth 8 points with W(4) giving strong base score. Top plays include DOWNLOAD, DOWNSIZE, DOWNTOWN.", "datePublished": "2026-06-23", "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" }, "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" }, "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-with-prefix-down" } })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({ "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [ { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the best DOWN prefix words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Top DOWN words include DOWNSIZE (21pts with Z), DOWNLOAD (13pts), DOWNTOWN (14pts), and DOWNHILL (15pts). DOWNSIZE is exceptional because Z(10) adds massive value. Most DOWN words use everyday vocabulary that's easy to spot." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many points is the DOWN prefix worth in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "DOWN is worth 8 points (D=2, O=1, W=4, N=1). The W tile alone contributes half the prefix value at 4 points, and D adds another 2. This makes DOWN one of the highest-scoring 4-tile prefixes, above MEGA (7pts), FORE (7pts), and SEMI (6pts)." } }, { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can DOWN words score bingos in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — DOWN is 4 tiles, so you need 3 more for a 7-letter bingo. DOWNIER hits exactly 7 letters. Longer extensions like DOWNLOAD (8 tiles), DOWNSIZE (8 tiles), and DOWNTOWN (8 tiles) all qualify for the 50-point bingo bonus, easily reaching 60-70+ points." } } ] })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Prefix Guides</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words with Prefix DOWN in Scrabble</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-23">June 23, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">DOWN is one of the highest-scoring 4-tile prefixes in Scrabble. With W(4) and D(2) providing 6 of the 8 total points, this prefix punches hard from the start. And the vocabulary is universally known — download, downtown, downhill, downturn. You'll never struggle to recognize a DOWN word on your rack because these are words you use every day.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Prefix Tiles</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Base Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid Extensions</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tiles to Bingo</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top DOWN Words by Score</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">DOWNSIZE — 21 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 letters. To reduce workforce. Z(10) makes this the premium DOWN word.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">DOWNHILL — 15 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 letters. Descending slope. H(4) adds to W's value for a solid bingo.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">DOWNTOWN — 14 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 letters. City center. Second W(4) makes this a double-W powerhouse.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">DOWNTURN — 12 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 letters. Economic decline. All common tiles after the prefix. Easy bingo.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More DOWN Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DOWNLOAD</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DOWNFALL</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DOWNWARD</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DOWNCAST</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why DOWN Scores So Well</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">DOWN's 8-point base is the <span class="text-white font-medium">highest among common 4-tile prefixes</span>. W(4) and D(2) together contribute 6 of those 8 points. What makes DOWN exceptional is that both high-value tiles (W and D) are followed by common letters (O, N) that are easy to pair. You get premium scoring without needing rare tiles.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">DOWN Bingo Strategy</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">W provides anchor scoring:</span> W is worth 4 points and there are only 2 in the bag. When you draw W with D-O-N, immediately think DOWN. The prefix is already among the highest-scoring you can form.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">DOWNSIZE with Z = 71pts:</span> D-O-W-N-S-I-Z-E scores 21 base + 50 bingo bonus = 71 points. If you hold DOWN and draw S-I-Z, you've hit a premium bingo.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Everyday vocabulary:</span> DOWNLOAD, DOWNTOWN, DOWNHILL — these are words from daily conversation. No obscure memorization required, just rack awareness.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">W on premium squares:</span> Place W on Double Letter for 8 points from one tile, or on a Double Word square to double the entire word's value. DOWN on DW alone scores 16 points.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">DOWN Scoring Breakdown</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">D</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">2 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-2 py-1.5 text-gray-500">+</span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">O</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">1 pt</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-2 py-1.5 text-gray-500">+</span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">W</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">4 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-2 py-1.5 text-gray-500">+</span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">N</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">1 pt</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-2 py-1.5 text-gray-500">=</span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">8</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">total</span></span>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-starting-with-over/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Starting with OVER: The Opposite Direction Prefix</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/words-with-prefix-ultra/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words with Prefix ULTRA: Common-Tile Bingo Machine</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find all DOWN words instantly — enter your tiles and see every valid play</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
